President Obama announced his intent to nominate three individuals to key Administration posts. Cyrus Amir-Mokri is nominated for Assistant Secretary for Financial Institutions, Department of the Treasury, and Member, Board of Directors of the National Consumer Cooperative Bank. He has experience in complex securities and antitrust litigation and has served as Senior Counsel to the Chairman of the Commodity Futures Trading Commission. Kathryn Keneally is nominated for Assistant Attorney General for the Tax Division, Department of Justice. She is a partner at the law firm Fulbright & Jaworski LLP and has over twenty-five years of experience in tax controversies and defending against allegations of tax fraud. Michael James Warren is nominated for Member, Board of Directors of the Overseas Private Investment Corporation. He is a Principal and Managing Board member of Albright Stonebridge Group and has experience in corporate development and strategic consulting.